WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.488 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.488 --> 00:00:04.960 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.960 --> 00:00:29.780 align:middle line:90%


00:00:29.780 --> 00:00:33.710 align:middle line:84%
>> I discovered that
to believe in humanity,

00:00:33.710 --> 00:00:37.690 align:middle line:84%
and to have the personal
decision that you will not let

00:00:37.690 --> 00:00:42.290 align:middle line:84%
evil and the misdoings of
others drag you down was very

00:00:42.290 --> 00:00:44.000 align:middle line:90%
fundamental.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:47.480 align:middle line:90%
Love is something extraordinary.

00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:51.910 align:middle line:84%
And we should pay more attention
to words like peace, hope,

00:00:51.910 --> 00:00:56.260 align:middle line:90%
faith, thankfulness, and so on.

00:00:56.260 --> 00:01:00.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Dr. Robert Muller
is a man of peace.

00:01:00.190 --> 00:01:02.650 align:middle line:84%
He labored behind the
scenes at the United Nations

00:01:02.650 --> 00:01:08.510 align:middle line:84%
for nearly 40 years before
his retirement in 1986.

00:01:08.510 --> 00:01:13.160 align:middle line:84%
A decade later in 1996, he
received the prestigious Albert

00:01:13.160 --> 00:01:16.580 align:middle line:84%
Schweitzer award for his
humanitarian efforts.

00:01:16.580 --> 00:01:21.050 align:middle line:84%
His unfailing energy in working
towards a world without borders

00:01:21.050 --> 00:01:25.910 align:middle line:84%
has earned him the
title of global citizen.

00:01:25.910 --> 00:01:30.500 align:middle line:84%
Robert George Muller
was born in 1923.

00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.650 align:middle line:84%
In his early years he lived
through political turmoil

00:01:33.650 --> 00:01:36.440 align:middle line:84%
in the Alsace-Lorraine
region of France.

00:01:36.440 --> 00:01:38.800 align:middle line:84%
Without moving, his
grandparents were

00:01:38.800 --> 00:01:43.040 align:middle line:84%
claimed as citizens of five
successive nationalities,

00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:47.000 align:middle line:84%
as this region was repeatedly
conquered, the result of three

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:48.980 align:middle line:90%
major European wars.

00:01:48.980 --> 00:01:51.590 align:middle line:84%
As a child, he often
looked out the window

00:01:51.590 --> 00:01:53.950 align:middle line:90%
at a border he could not cross.

00:01:53.950 --> 00:01:58.190 align:middle line:10%
And dreamed of the day when he,
like the clouds and the birds,

00:01:58.190 --> 00:02:01.741 align:middle line:10%
would not have to be confined
by man-made divisions.

00:02:01.741 --> 00:02:05.669 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:02:05.669 --> 00:02:08.620 align:middle line:90%


00:02:08.620 --> 00:02:13.030 align:middle line:84%
>> During World War II Mr.
Muller experienced the horrors

00:02:13.030 --> 00:02:15.520 align:middle line:90%
of war.

00:02:15.520 --> 00:02:19.050 align:middle line:84%
First, as a member of
the French resistance,

00:02:19.050 --> 00:02:21.960 align:middle line:84%
where he endured
the Nazi occupation.

00:02:21.960 --> 00:02:25.440 align:middle line:84%
Then he suffered as
a prisoner of war.

00:02:25.440 --> 00:02:28.500 align:middle line:90%
And later, became a refugee.

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:30.750 align:middle line:10%
When he finally
returned home, he

00:02:30.750 --> 00:02:33.390 align:middle line:10%
enrolled in the
University of Strasbourg,

00:02:33.390 --> 00:02:35.250 align:middle line:10%
earning a doctorate of law.

00:02:35.250 --> 00:02:39.000 align:middle line:10%
Then in 1948 he entered
an essay contest,

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:42.850 align:middle line:10%
writing about how to
best govern the world.

00:02:42.850 --> 00:02:47.140 align:middle line:84%
He won first prize, an
internship at the newly created

00:02:47.140 --> 00:02:48.850 align:middle line:90%
United Nations.

00:02:48.850 --> 00:02:53.440 align:middle line:84%
For the next four decades Dr.
Muller met with world leaders,

00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:56.380 align:middle line:84%
looking at humanity from
a global perspective,

00:02:56.380 --> 00:03:00.820 align:middle line:84%
and envisioning ways to improve
life on the planet Earth.

00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:04.000 align:middle line:84%
He rose to the ranks at the
UN, and eventually became

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:07.360 align:middle line:84%
an assistant to the
Secretary General.

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:10.300 align:middle line:84%
Because of his optimistic
views about man's ability

00:03:10.300 --> 00:03:13.600 align:middle line:84%
to live in peace and
take care of the Earth,

00:03:13.600 --> 00:03:18.110 align:middle line:84%
he is known as the
"Prophet of Hope."

00:03:18.110 --> 00:03:21.440 align:middle line:10%
>> Dr. Muller, what a pleasure
and a privilege it is for me

00:03:21.440 --> 00:03:23.010 align:middle line:10%
to sit down and talk with you.

00:03:23.010 --> 00:03:24.710 align:middle line:90%
I thank you so much.

00:03:24.710 --> 00:03:27.440 align:middle line:90%
You have accomplished so much.

00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:32.090 align:middle line:10%
You have lived the life of three
men, as far as I'm concerned,

00:03:32.090 --> 00:03:33.950 align:middle line:10%
with all that you have
done in your life.

00:03:33.950 --> 00:03:37.310 align:middle line:84%
But the basis of all you
do and all you write about

00:03:37.310 --> 00:03:38.300 align:middle line:90%
is happiness.

00:03:38.300 --> 00:03:39.380 align:middle line:90%
Is that true?

00:03:39.380 --> 00:03:40.760 align:middle line:90%
>> That's correct.

00:03:40.760 --> 00:03:41.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Why happiness?

00:03:41.630 --> 00:03:46.430 align:middle line:84%
Why not ambition, or
drive, or dissatisfaction?

00:03:46.430 --> 00:03:50.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think it was a
perception I had as a child

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:52.070 align:middle line:90%
already.

00:03:52.070 --> 00:03:55.880 align:middle line:84%
My father told me that
when I was a four-year-old

00:03:55.880 --> 00:04:00.500 align:middle line:84%
I was going around saying
that life was divine.

00:04:00.500 --> 00:04:03.505 align:middle line:84%
And I took this word
"divine," because it

00:04:03.505 --> 00:04:08.160 align:middle line:84%
was the biggest objective I
could find to give my view of

00:04:08.160 --> 00:04:08.960 align:middle line:90%
to be alive.

00:04:08.960 --> 00:04:13.430 align:middle line:84%
For me to be alive was something
absolutely extraordinary.

00:04:13.430 --> 00:04:15.150 align:middle line:90%
To see old people.

00:04:15.150 --> 00:04:17.779 align:middle line:84%
My father was surprised that
I took off my cap each time

00:04:17.779 --> 00:04:20.620 align:middle line:84%
there was an old man,
all the old ladies.

00:04:20.620 --> 00:04:21.950 align:middle line:90%
Why you do that?

00:04:21.950 --> 00:04:23.720 align:middle line:90%
Because they know so much.

00:04:23.720 --> 00:04:25.880 align:middle line:84%
And I hope that some
day I will know as

00:04:25.880 --> 00:04:28.340 align:middle line:90%
much as these old people know.

00:04:28.340 --> 00:04:33.290 align:middle line:84%
So for me, life was something
absolutely extraordinary.

00:04:33.290 --> 00:04:36.740 align:middle line:84%
And by having this
feeling towards life,

00:04:36.740 --> 00:04:40.160 align:middle line:84%
I felt that happiness
was almost a duty.

00:04:40.160 --> 00:04:44.720 align:middle line:84%
I was a happy child,
because all this around me

00:04:44.720 --> 00:04:47.300 align:middle line:90%
was an incredible miracle.

00:04:47.300 --> 00:04:52.640 align:middle line:84%
For me, happiness is still the
objective of the human being.

00:04:52.640 --> 00:04:57.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think that people
can make a conscious decision

00:04:57.680 --> 00:05:00.290 align:middle line:84%
to become happy if
they are not happy?

00:05:00.290 --> 00:05:01.100 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, definitely.

00:05:01.100 --> 00:05:04.310 align:middle line:84%
And this has happened to
me quite a number of times.

00:05:04.310 --> 00:05:08.330 align:middle line:84%
At one point the Germans stopped
me at the border, arrested me,

00:05:08.330 --> 00:05:10.730 align:middle line:90%
and we were in a Gestapo prison.

00:05:10.730 --> 00:05:12.950 align:middle line:90%
And we couldn't even lie down.

00:05:12.950 --> 00:05:15.350 align:middle line:90%
It was filled with people.

00:05:15.350 --> 00:05:20.360 align:middle line:84%
And you had a pail somewhere
for doing your necessities.

00:05:20.360 --> 00:05:24.140 align:middle line:84%
It was so awful I couldn't
imagine that something

00:05:24.140 --> 00:05:26.330 align:middle line:90%
like this could happen.

00:05:26.330 --> 00:05:30.290 align:middle line:84%
And then I said, how can I be
happy in a place like this?

00:05:30.290 --> 00:05:32.150 align:middle line:90%
That's impossible.

00:05:32.150 --> 00:05:33.620 align:middle line:90%
And I said, no.

00:05:33.620 --> 00:05:35.640 align:middle line:90%
I can decide to be happy.

00:05:35.640 --> 00:05:37.590 align:middle line:90%
But how would you do that?

00:05:37.590 --> 00:05:40.400 align:middle line:84%
It just happened that
I had a pencil, which

00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:42.890 align:middle line:90%
they didn't take off my coat.

00:05:42.890 --> 00:05:45.360 align:middle line:84%
And then I went
through the prison.

00:05:45.360 --> 00:05:47.930 align:middle line:84%
I also said, let
me go to the door.

00:05:47.930 --> 00:05:49.940 align:middle line:84%
And then I was
there at the door.

00:05:49.940 --> 00:05:54.170 align:middle line:84%
And with this pencil
I wrote a novel.

00:05:54.170 --> 00:05:58.010 align:middle line:84%
And I imagined that I was
living on a hill falling

00:05:58.010 --> 00:06:03.050 align:middle line:84%
in love with a beautiful girl,
and I was out of this prison.

00:06:03.050 --> 00:06:06.740 align:middle line:84%
I decided to be with
my mind elsewhere.

00:06:06.740 --> 00:06:11.420 align:middle line:84%
And as a result of this, I
was happy even in that prison.

00:06:11.420 --> 00:06:14.510 align:middle line:90%
They couldn't get my happiness.

00:06:14.510 --> 00:06:19.020 align:middle line:84%
>> People watching this
broadcast would say,

00:06:19.020 --> 00:06:20.820 align:middle line:90%
I like the idea.

00:06:20.820 --> 00:06:22.110 align:middle line:90%
I like the concept.

00:06:22.110 --> 00:06:24.480 align:middle line:90%
But I am unhappy.

00:06:24.480 --> 00:06:26.340 align:middle line:90%
I want to find happiness.

00:06:26.340 --> 00:06:29.730 align:middle line:84%
I have a dream that
I want to come true.

00:06:29.730 --> 00:06:32.760 align:middle line:84%
What's the first
step that person

00:06:32.760 --> 00:06:35.710 align:middle line:90%
takes to go in that direction?

00:06:35.710 --> 00:06:38.260 align:middle line:84%
>> I think there
would be two things.

00:06:38.260 --> 00:06:42.520 align:middle line:84%
The first one is to
remember your early youth.

00:06:42.520 --> 00:06:45.420 align:middle line:84%
What was your dream
when you were a child?

00:06:45.420 --> 00:06:49.890 align:middle line:84%
That gives you an idea
of what you can still do,

00:06:49.890 --> 00:06:53.970 align:middle line:84%
even if society has put
you into another direction.

00:06:53.970 --> 00:06:55.920 align:middle line:84%
And you can do it even
when you're very old,

00:06:55.920 --> 00:06:58.050 align:middle line:84%
when you're free,
when you are retired.

00:06:58.050 --> 00:07:01.030 align:middle line:84%
That's what I always
say to the old people.

00:07:01.030 --> 00:07:05.070 align:middle line:84%
Fulfill now the dream you
had when you were a child.

00:07:05.070 --> 00:07:09.780 align:middle line:84%
And once you see this, and
once you have your dream

00:07:09.780 --> 00:07:14.370 align:middle line:84%
and begin to work on it, then
you're immediately uplifted.

00:07:14.370 --> 00:07:16.140 align:middle line:90%
And you find the happiness.

00:07:16.140 --> 00:07:18.150 align:middle line:84%
And the funny thing is
that usually the dream

00:07:18.150 --> 00:07:19.680 align:middle line:90%
becomes fulfilled.

00:07:19.680 --> 00:07:22.500 align:middle line:84%
In my case, I was
dreaming as a kid

00:07:22.500 --> 00:07:25.980 align:middle line:84%
that the border which I saw
from my window disappeared.

00:07:25.980 --> 00:07:28.920 align:middle line:90%
And it disappeared.

00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:30.510 align:middle line:90%
>> So then dreams have power.

00:07:30.510 --> 00:07:38.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Dreams are some extraordinary
expansion of your capacities,

00:07:38.010 --> 00:07:42.270 align:middle line:84%
and what you could be able
to do if you do not see

00:07:42.270 --> 00:07:43.950 align:middle line:90%
the obstacles.

00:07:43.950 --> 00:07:48.891 align:middle line:84%
And when you dream then
there comes the idea.

00:07:48.891 --> 00:07:50.790 align:middle line:90%
The idea follows the dream.

00:07:50.790 --> 00:07:53.910 align:middle line:84%
Well, after having the dream,
this is what you can do.

00:07:53.910 --> 00:07:56.120 align:middle line:90%
Why don't you start with this?

00:07:56.120 --> 00:08:00.840 align:middle line:84%
So that the idea is a concrete
manifestation of the way

00:08:00.840 --> 00:08:04.230 align:middle line:90%
of fulfilling your dream.

00:08:04.230 --> 00:08:08.020 align:middle line:84%
And this is why I've written
all the thousands of ideas.

00:08:08.020 --> 00:08:11.850 align:middle line:84%
And if they do not come
into practice immediately,

00:08:11.850 --> 00:08:12.900 align:middle line:90%
it might be later.

00:08:12.900 --> 00:08:15.510 align:middle line:84%
It might even be
after your death.

00:08:15.510 --> 00:08:18.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Speaking of those
dreams, let's look at them.

00:08:18.220 --> 00:08:20.850 align:middle line:84%
Because I've read
some of your dreams

00:08:20.850 --> 00:08:22.600 align:middle line:90%
that you have written about.

00:08:22.600 --> 00:08:25.140 align:middle line:84%
And there are a couple
that I particularly love.

00:08:25.140 --> 00:08:28.890 align:middle line:84%
And I want to know how you
think they can come true.

00:08:28.890 --> 00:08:33.480 align:middle line:10%
This is from your book of "Ideas
and Dreams for a Better World."

00:08:33.480 --> 00:08:37.500 align:middle line:90%
Idea number 1,859.

00:08:37.500 --> 00:08:38.850 align:middle line:90%
You're right, Dr. Muller.

00:08:38.850 --> 00:08:42.390 align:middle line:84%
You do have quite a
few ideas and dreams.

00:08:42.390 --> 00:08:46.110 align:middle line:10%
"Wonder has been a
permanent part of my being

00:08:46.110 --> 00:08:48.030 align:middle line:10%
during my life.

00:08:48.030 --> 00:08:53.370 align:middle line:10%
In my elderly years it
has reached its maximum.

00:08:53.370 --> 00:08:57.330 align:middle line:84%
Have a sense of wonder for
your magical, divine life.

00:08:57.330 --> 00:09:00.390 align:middle line:84%
And for all the miracles
that surround you."

00:09:00.390 --> 00:09:02.860 align:middle line:84%
Talk to me about how we can
find wonder in our lives

00:09:02.860 --> 00:09:04.050 align:middle line:90%
if we don't have it.

00:09:04.050 --> 00:09:07.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it's again a
creation of your being.

00:09:07.180 --> 00:09:10.740 align:middle line:84%
You see, maybe for a
long period of my life

00:09:10.740 --> 00:09:14.490 align:middle line:84%
I was not thinking
in terms of wonder.

00:09:14.490 --> 00:09:18.690 align:middle line:84%
As we talked about
before, I was dreaming.

00:09:18.690 --> 00:09:23.680 align:middle line:84%
I had a feeling of
the miracle of life.

00:09:23.680 --> 00:09:28.500 align:middle line:84%
And as I got older and
older, and wrote this,

00:09:28.500 --> 00:09:34.800 align:middle line:84%
I found another dimension
is the dimension of wonder.

00:09:34.800 --> 00:09:36.570 align:middle line:84%
It is that when
you wake up and you

00:09:36.570 --> 00:09:38.580 align:middle line:84%
look at the sky in
the morning, and you

00:09:38.580 --> 00:09:45.120 align:middle line:84%
see the forest in Costa Rica
being awaken under the sun,

00:09:45.120 --> 00:09:48.300 align:middle line:90%
this is almost a dream.

00:09:48.300 --> 00:09:50.160 align:middle line:90%
It is a miracle.

00:09:50.160 --> 00:09:52.620 align:middle line:84%
But what it does to
me as a human being

00:09:52.620 --> 00:09:54.720 align:middle line:90%
is a sense of wonder.

00:09:54.720 --> 00:09:58.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Would it help us, Dr.
Muller, if we asked the universe

00:09:58.980 --> 00:10:02.220 align:middle line:84%
or a power greater
than ourselves, or God,

00:10:02.220 --> 00:10:03.750 align:middle line:90%
show me a sense of wonder.

00:10:03.750 --> 00:10:05.580 align:middle line:84%
Give it to me so
that I may have it.

00:10:05.580 --> 00:10:06.660 align:middle line:90%
>> And you'll get it.

00:10:06.660 --> 00:10:07.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Then I'll get it.

00:10:07.540 --> 00:10:08.800 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:08.800 --> 00:10:13.800 align:middle line:90%
Idea number 1,782.

00:10:13.800 --> 00:10:18.240 align:middle line:84%
"The word 'retirement
age' should be abolished,

00:10:18.240 --> 00:10:24.020 align:middle line:84%
and be replaced by a new
word like 'fulfillment age.'"

00:10:24.020 --> 00:10:27.570 align:middle line:90%
>> I even call it "refirement."

00:10:27.570 --> 00:10:28.840 align:middle line:90%
>> I like that.

00:10:28.840 --> 00:10:29.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:10:29.640 --> 00:10:34.470 align:middle line:84%
I cannot accept to
retire from anything.

00:10:34.470 --> 00:10:37.820 align:middle line:84%
And when I left the
United Nations I said now

00:10:37.820 --> 00:10:40.500 align:middle line:90%
I have total freedom.

00:10:40.500 --> 00:10:43.060 align:middle line:90%
And I am now 77 years old.

00:10:43.060 --> 00:10:45.490 align:middle line:90%
I've never felt so good.

00:10:45.490 --> 00:10:47.800 align:middle line:84%
I am free at the
University for Peace.

00:10:47.800 --> 00:10:50.640 align:middle line:84%
I work there for one dollar a
year so they cannot give me any

00:10:50.640 --> 00:10:51.530 align:middle line:90%
order.

00:10:51.530 --> 00:10:53.630 align:middle line:90%
I give my free services.

00:10:53.630 --> 00:10:56.610 align:middle line:84%
I am in Costa Rica in a
demilitarized country.

00:10:56.610 --> 00:11:00.900 align:middle line:84%
I can write, I can come up with
my dreams, I can make speeches.

00:11:00.900 --> 00:11:03.510 align:middle line:84%
I can walk in a
wonderful nature.

00:11:03.510 --> 00:11:06.120 align:middle line:90%
And this is not retirement.

00:11:06.120 --> 00:11:09.570 align:middle line:84%
In other words, even when I
was in the big United Nations

00:11:09.570 --> 00:11:12.730 align:middle line:90%
I was on top of the world.

00:11:12.730 --> 00:11:16.890 align:middle line:84%
But after leaving the United
Nations I didn't lose anything.

00:11:16.890 --> 00:11:20.520 align:middle line:84%
I found the whole nature of
Costa Rica, of the tropics

00:11:20.520 --> 00:11:21.700 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:11:21.700 --> 00:11:24.780 align:middle line:84%
So that with my leaving
the United Nations

00:11:24.780 --> 00:11:27.780 align:middle line:84%
I found even an expansion
of my own being.

00:11:27.780 --> 00:11:32.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Dr. Muller, I find you
to be a man who is so alive.

00:11:32.700 --> 00:11:34.740 align:middle line:90%
Are you at all afraid of dying?

00:11:34.740 --> 00:11:37.440 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't like
the idea of dying.

00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:43.200 align:middle line:84%
But first of all, by
taking this attitude

00:11:43.200 --> 00:11:47.820 align:middle line:84%
of having so much to do, so
many dreams, so many ideas,

00:11:47.820 --> 00:11:49.830 align:middle line:90%
you have no time to get sick.

00:11:49.830 --> 00:11:51.720 align:middle line:90%
And you have no time to get old.

00:11:51.720 --> 00:11:54.270 align:middle line:84%
So the idea of being
old is completely

00:11:54.270 --> 00:11:56.190 align:middle line:90%
excluded from my mind.

00:11:56.190 --> 00:12:00.510 align:middle line:84%
And I pray God to let me live
as long as possible in order

00:12:00.510 --> 00:12:03.170 align:middle line:90%
to do as much as possible.

00:12:03.170 --> 00:12:06.750 align:middle line:84%
And I live in such
a way to be healthy,

00:12:06.750 --> 00:12:08.940 align:middle line:84%
and not to take
any drugs, alcohol,

00:12:08.940 --> 00:12:12.030 align:middle line:84%
or things of this sort,
to sleep from 7 o'clock

00:12:12.030 --> 00:12:14.100 align:middle line:84%
in the evening and
nine hours every night,

00:12:14.100 --> 00:12:17.950 align:middle line:84%
because I go to bed at a time
when the roosters go to bed.

00:12:17.950 --> 00:12:20.130 align:middle line:84%
And then they wake me up
at 4:00 in the morning

00:12:20.130 --> 00:12:23.190 align:middle line:84%
so that I am in tune
with the nature.

00:12:23.190 --> 00:12:26.190 align:middle line:90%
And to live as long as possible.

00:12:26.190 --> 00:12:31.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Idea 1,902.

00:12:31.530 --> 00:12:35.730 align:middle line:10%
Every UN delegate, speaking,
should have before him a heart

00:12:35.730 --> 00:12:39.630 align:middle line:10%
stick like the
indigenous people have,

00:12:39.630 --> 00:12:43.930 align:middle line:10%
to remind them that they
should speak from the heart.

00:12:43.930 --> 00:12:47.620 align:middle line:84%
And you even say, "I
use such a stick."

00:12:47.620 --> 00:12:50.370 align:middle line:84%
Tell me about this stick and
how it would help the world.

00:12:50.370 --> 00:12:55.120 align:middle line:84%
>> It is to remind you
always that when you speak,

00:12:55.120 --> 00:12:57.930 align:middle line:84%
you must also speak
with the heart.

00:12:57.930 --> 00:13:02.640 align:middle line:84%
Because we Westerners will speak
mostly with the intelligence.

00:13:02.640 --> 00:13:08.580 align:middle line:84%
And very seldom do we dare
to use the word "love."

00:13:08.580 --> 00:13:10.830 align:middle line:84%
Recently, at the
University for Peace,

00:13:10.830 --> 00:13:14.970 align:middle line:84%
at the end of a course,
a girl student, when

00:13:14.970 --> 00:13:20.280 align:middle line:84%
I ended the course with a
speech as the chancellor,

00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:23.790 align:middle line:84%
she said, Mr. Muller, you do
not know how much I thank you.

00:13:23.790 --> 00:13:27.240 align:middle line:84%
Because I've taken this
three-months course and I've

00:13:27.240 --> 00:13:29.370 align:middle line:90%
never heard the word "love."

00:13:29.370 --> 00:13:33.800 align:middle line:84%
And in your final speech
you used it three times.

00:13:33.800 --> 00:13:36.170 align:middle line:90%
Can you imagine?

00:13:36.170 --> 00:13:39.050 align:middle line:84%
The distance between
the brain and the heart

00:13:39.050 --> 00:13:41.180 align:middle line:90%
is only 18 inches.

00:13:41.180 --> 00:13:44.630 align:middle line:84%
So you have to make a conduit
between the heart upstairs.

00:13:44.630 --> 00:13:46.910 align:middle line:90%
And the stick reminds you--

00:13:46.910 --> 00:13:51.410 align:middle line:84%
reminds indigenous people
never to forget the heart.

00:13:51.410 --> 00:13:54.800 align:middle line:84%
And our Western society
is too cerebral.

00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:56.470 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't speak enough of love.

00:13:56.470 --> 00:13:59.150 align:middle line:84%
We should speak about
love, happiness.

00:13:59.150 --> 00:14:00.530 align:middle line:90%
All these great concepts.

00:14:00.530 --> 00:14:01.640 align:middle line:90%
Forgiveness.

00:14:01.640 --> 00:14:03.200 align:middle line:90%
Compassion.

00:14:03.200 --> 00:14:04.760 align:middle line:90%
Taking care of people.

00:14:04.760 --> 00:14:06.410 align:middle line:84%
These are the great
concepts which

00:14:06.410 --> 00:14:10.610 align:middle line:90%
have always guided humanity.

00:14:10.610 --> 00:14:13.460 align:middle line:84%
And one thing which
is also important,

00:14:13.460 --> 00:14:16.280 align:middle line:84%
and which I remember
from youth, it

00:14:16.280 --> 00:14:20.310 align:middle line:84%
is to be in union
with the universe.

00:14:20.310 --> 00:14:23.100 align:middle line:84%
In other words, not only the
total planet and the total

00:14:23.100 --> 00:14:24.600 align:middle line:90%
humanity, but the universe.

00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:27.030 align:middle line:84%
And this I got,
again, as a child.

00:14:27.030 --> 00:14:30.090 align:middle line:84%
>> But what you're talking
about is a reverence for life.

00:14:30.090 --> 00:14:31.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Reverence for life.

00:14:31.080 --> 00:14:31.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course.

00:14:31.500 --> 00:14:31.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:14:31.970 --> 00:14:33.060 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:14:33.060 --> 00:14:35.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Is what's happening
right now a dream?

00:14:35.940 --> 00:14:40.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Again, it's a dream that
I'm able to tell you this.

00:14:40.200 --> 00:14:42.600 align:middle line:84%
Because my dream
is that really what

00:14:42.600 --> 00:14:46.920 align:middle line:84%
I have learned from life,
these extraordinary lessons,

00:14:46.920 --> 00:14:49.830 align:middle line:84%
at the end of the 20th
century and the [INAUDIBLE],,

00:14:49.830 --> 00:14:52.350 align:middle line:84%
I would like to give
this to the world.

00:14:52.350 --> 00:14:56.700 align:middle line:84%
I would like to make the whole
world learn how to be happy,

00:14:56.700 --> 00:15:01.080 align:middle line:84%
and not to think negatively,
to think always optimistically

00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:02.010 align:middle line:90%
and positively.

00:15:02.010 --> 00:15:04.830 align:middle line:84%
Because optimistic
is always better,

00:15:04.830 --> 00:15:07.200 align:middle line:84%
even if it does not
succeed than pessimism.

00:15:07.200 --> 00:15:09.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Let me ask you this.

00:15:09.640 --> 00:15:12.610 align:middle line:90%
Give yourself a progress report.

00:15:12.610 --> 00:15:15.070 align:middle line:90%
How are you doing on your dream?

00:15:15.070 --> 00:15:18.190 align:middle line:84%
Your desire to teach
us, to teach the world

00:15:18.190 --> 00:15:22.930 align:middle line:84%
not to think negatively, to open
yourself to the cosmic forces.

00:15:22.930 --> 00:15:24.910 align:middle line:84%
How are you doing on
your mission, doctor?

00:15:24.910 --> 00:15:27.670 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, it's not yet very far.

00:15:27.670 --> 00:15:32.110 align:middle line:10%
But it is much better than
I could have ever expected.

00:15:32.110 --> 00:15:37.270 align:middle line:84%
If anyone would have told me
that the border in my home town

00:15:37.270 --> 00:15:39.040 align:middle line:90%
would disappear--

00:15:39.040 --> 00:15:42.580 align:middle line:84%
if anyone would have told
me that I would survive

00:15:42.580 --> 00:15:45.760 align:middle line:84%
all the Gestapos and
the Second World War,

00:15:45.760 --> 00:15:48.880 align:middle line:84%
where I could have been
killed a half a dozen times--

00:15:48.880 --> 00:15:52.570 align:middle line:84%
if anyone would have told me
that my dream to work for peace

00:15:52.570 --> 00:15:55.480 align:middle line:84%
would be fulfilled, and that
I would enter the United

00:15:55.480 --> 00:15:58.510 align:middle line:84%
Nations with an essay
immediately after the Second

00:15:58.510 --> 00:16:02.770 align:middle line:84%
World War-- and that three days
before retiring from the United

00:16:02.770 --> 00:16:06.670 align:middle line:84%
Nations I would be appointed
the Chancellor of a University

00:16:06.670 --> 00:16:09.160 align:middle line:84%
for Peace in a
demilitarized country.

00:16:09.160 --> 00:16:09.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow!

00:16:09.970 --> 00:16:13.450 align:middle line:84%
>> And that there are 34 Robert
Muller schools who are teaching

00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:16.510 align:middle line:84%
the children what
we are saying here.

00:16:16.510 --> 00:16:18.850 align:middle line:90%
To teach them happiness.

00:16:18.850 --> 00:16:22.180 align:middle line:84%
There's a Robert Muller school
which I visited in Texas.

00:16:22.180 --> 00:16:25.102 align:middle line:84%
And then the caretaker
in the courtyard

00:16:25.102 --> 00:16:26.560 align:middle line:84%
said, Mr. Muller,
I don't know what

00:16:26.560 --> 00:16:28.720 align:middle line:84%
they are teaching to
these children in there,

00:16:28.720 --> 00:16:32.030 align:middle line:84%
but I've never seen two
children fight each other.

00:16:32.030 --> 00:16:33.940 align:middle line:90%
How do they succeed this?

00:16:33.940 --> 00:16:35.650 align:middle line:84%
And I said for a
very simple reason.

00:16:35.650 --> 00:16:38.470 align:middle line:84%
Because on the day the
children come to the schools--

00:16:38.470 --> 00:16:42.940 align:middle line:84%
and the mothers already
tell them in their womb,

00:16:42.940 --> 00:16:46.170 align:middle line:84%
they are told that
they are a miracle.

00:16:46.170 --> 00:16:48.540 align:middle line:84%
And that they should be happy
to be alive when we know

00:16:48.540 --> 00:16:50.040 align:middle line:90%
so much about the universe.

00:16:50.040 --> 00:16:52.830 align:middle line:84%
More than any king
and emperor in time.

00:16:52.830 --> 00:16:55.445 align:middle line:84%
They should be proud
to be alive today.

00:16:55.445 --> 00:16:56.820 align:middle line:84%
And that they will
have a great--

00:16:56.820 --> 00:16:59.610 align:middle line:84%
they can have a
great role in life.

00:16:59.610 --> 00:17:02.580 align:middle line:84%
And then the children, they
say, well, if I'm a miracle

00:17:02.580 --> 00:17:05.760 align:middle line:84%
and he's a miracle how
can I hurt a miracle?

00:17:05.760 --> 00:17:08.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Then I would say that your
progress report is a pretty

00:17:08.940 --> 00:17:09.750 align:middle line:90%
good one.

00:17:09.750 --> 00:17:10.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Not bad.

00:17:10.850 --> 00:17:11.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Not bad.

00:17:11.650 --> 00:17:12.608 align:middle line:90%
>> But not good enough.

