00:17:23.920 --> 00:17:27.550 align:middle line:84%
>> During his four decades
at the United Nations, Dr.

00:17:27.550 --> 00:17:32.320 align:middle line:84%
Muller watched it grow from a
gathering of a mere 51 nations

00:17:32.320 --> 00:17:35.650 align:middle line:90%
to become a world authority.

00:17:35.650 --> 00:17:37.930 align:middle line:84%
He presided over early
efforts to conduct

00:17:37.930 --> 00:17:41.290 align:middle line:90%
a worldwide population count.

00:17:41.290 --> 00:17:44.220 align:middle line:84%
He projected birth rates,
and medical advances

00:17:44.220 --> 00:17:47.010 align:middle line:90%
that would increase longevity.

00:17:47.010 --> 00:17:49.170 align:middle line:84%
He warned of the
potential difficulties

00:17:49.170 --> 00:17:53.620 align:middle line:84%
to the biosphere with
uncontrolled population growth.

00:17:53.620 --> 00:17:56.670 align:middle line:10%
And then in 1972,
he presided over

00:17:56.670 --> 00:17:59.460 align:middle line:10%
the first worldwide
conference on the environment

00:17:59.460 --> 00:18:03.190 align:middle line:10%
held in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.

00:18:03.190 --> 00:18:05.530 align:middle line:10%
One of your great
accomplishments, Dr. Muller,

00:18:05.530 --> 00:18:11.410 align:middle line:10%
is more than 40 years of
service with the United Nations.

00:18:11.410 --> 00:18:13.840 align:middle line:90%
I think that's remarkable.

00:18:13.840 --> 00:18:17.940 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people today, though,
say that the UN is outdated,

00:18:17.940 --> 00:18:20.680 align:middle line:84%
and there is no longer
a need for that.

00:18:20.680 --> 00:18:22.970 align:middle line:90%
What are your thoughts on that?

00:18:22.970 --> 00:18:25.670 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, the United
Nations, in my opinion,

00:18:25.670 --> 00:18:30.010 align:middle line:10%
is really probably one of the
most important things that has

00:18:30.010 --> 00:18:32.350 align:middle line:10%
happened in this century.

00:18:32.350 --> 00:18:37.560 align:middle line:84%
When the World War II was
over and I joined the UN

00:18:37.560 --> 00:18:40.600 align:middle line:84%
I was a very
pessimistic young man.

00:18:40.600 --> 00:18:42.700 align:middle line:90%
If the French and the Germans--

00:18:42.700 --> 00:18:46.030 align:middle line:84%
two white highly
civilized countries--

00:18:46.030 --> 00:18:52.000 align:middle line:84%
had three wars in the lifetime
of my grandparents and parents,

00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:58.410 align:middle line:84%
how can I expect that communists
and capitalists, rich and poor,

00:18:58.410 --> 00:19:02.170 align:middle line:84%
to thousands of religions,
so many ethnic groups

00:19:02.170 --> 00:19:05.050 align:middle line:84%
and languages, that they
are going to make it?

00:19:05.050 --> 00:19:07.390 align:middle line:84%
I was almost sure
that within 20 years

00:19:07.390 --> 00:19:10.540 align:middle line:84%
there would be something
else that would trigger off

00:19:10.540 --> 00:19:12.130 align:middle line:90%
World War III.

00:19:12.130 --> 00:19:14.050 align:middle line:90%
And it hasn't happened.

00:19:14.050 --> 00:19:17.020 align:middle line:84%
When I go to New York
in the first United

00:19:17.020 --> 00:19:19.900 align:middle line:84%
Nations in an
abandoned war factory,

00:19:19.900 --> 00:19:23.240 align:middle line:84%
a Belgian delegate asked me,
what you're coming to do here,

00:19:23.240 --> 00:19:24.740 align:middle line:90%
young man?

00:19:24.740 --> 00:19:26.350 align:middle line:84%
I said, I come here
to work for peace,

00:19:26.350 --> 00:19:28.780 align:middle line:84%
because I do not
want my children

00:19:28.780 --> 00:19:32.110 align:middle line:84%
to see the horrors I
have seen in this war.

00:19:32.110 --> 00:19:35.530 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, I pity you,
because you will lose your job.

00:19:35.530 --> 00:19:39.700 align:middle line:84%
This organization will not
last more than five years.

00:19:39.700 --> 00:19:44.060 align:middle line:84%
And the United Nations still
exists, has become universal.

00:19:44.060 --> 00:19:46.570 align:middle line:84%
It's the metabiological
organization

00:19:46.570 --> 00:19:49.870 align:middle line:84%
of the human species that
has to look into everything.

00:19:49.870 --> 00:19:53.440 align:middle line:84%
The outer space, the population,
the climate of the world,

00:19:53.440 --> 00:19:55.120 align:middle line:90%
the future population.

00:19:55.120 --> 00:19:57.880 align:middle line:84%
What will the world
be in 100 years?

00:19:57.880 --> 00:19:59.510 align:middle line:90%
In 1,000 years.

00:19:59.510 --> 00:20:05.470 align:middle line:84%
It is the biggest central
brain of the human species.

00:20:05.470 --> 00:20:11.800 align:middle line:84%
>> What if there was a
world symposium somewhere,

00:20:11.800 --> 00:20:17.260 align:middle line:84%
specifically about global
consciousness and spirituality?

00:20:17.260 --> 00:20:18.470 align:middle line:90%
Would people come to that?

00:20:18.470 --> 00:20:19.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:20:19.270 --> 00:20:24.880 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, I have
created, with Dr. Karan Singh

00:20:24.880 --> 00:20:30.100 align:middle line:84%
of India, a World Commission
of Eminent Personalities

00:20:30.100 --> 00:20:33.790 align:middle line:84%
on Global Consciousness
and Spirituality.

00:20:33.790 --> 00:20:35.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, it's done then.

00:20:35.500 --> 00:20:38.380 align:middle line:84%
>> And we are going
to have a meeting,

00:20:38.380 --> 00:20:44.910 align:middle line:84%
which is planned now in Spain
in October of next year,

00:20:44.910 --> 00:20:48.460 align:middle line:84%
to bring together the most
eminent people from around

00:20:48.460 --> 00:20:52.900 align:middle line:84%
the world in order to
look precisely into this.

00:20:52.900 --> 00:20:55.660 align:middle line:84%
Namely to have the
consciousness of the universe,

00:20:55.660 --> 00:20:59.620 align:middle line:84%
the consciousness of
our planet, and to have

00:20:59.620 --> 00:21:03.610 align:middle line:84%
the religions to cooperate
in this global consciousness.

00:21:03.610 --> 00:21:04.410 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:21:04.410 --> 00:21:05.830 align:middle line:90%
Create your dream.

00:21:05.830 --> 00:21:07.150 align:middle line:90%
Who would you like to be there?

00:21:07.150 --> 00:21:08.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we will
invite presidents.

00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:10.330 align:middle line:90%
We'll invite the Dalai Lama.

00:21:10.330 --> 00:21:12.550 align:middle line:84%
We'll invite the Secretary
General of the UN.

00:21:12.550 --> 00:21:15.280 align:middle line:84%
We have some of the
best thinkers on Earth

00:21:15.280 --> 00:21:17.760 align:middle line:84%
who are perhaps
not so much known.

00:21:17.760 --> 00:21:20.050 align:middle line:84%
We will invite Ted Turner
and people like this

00:21:20.050 --> 00:21:25.510 align:middle line:84%
to really reach finally
this global consciousness

00:21:25.510 --> 00:21:26.800 align:middle line:90%
of the human species.

00:21:26.800 --> 00:21:29.080 align:middle line:90%
Beyond the nations.

00:21:29.080 --> 00:21:30.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Is that possible?

00:21:30.970 --> 00:21:32.200 align:middle line:90%
>> We have to do it.

00:21:32.200 --> 00:21:35.300 align:middle line:84%
Again, do not consider
anything impossible.

00:21:35.300 --> 00:21:38.800 align:middle line:84%
This is why I speak so much
about the world in my books,

00:21:38.800 --> 00:21:41.230 align:middle line:90%
and for 18 books so far.

00:21:41.230 --> 00:21:44.230 align:middle line:84%
And then my 4,000
ideas is always this.

00:21:44.230 --> 00:21:47.907 align:middle line:84%
You must love the
earth as your home.

00:21:47.907 --> 00:21:49.240 align:middle line:90%
>> You're a good teacher for me.

00:21:49.240 --> 00:21:52.000 align:middle line:84%
Because I, like many people
watching this broadcast,

00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:56.180 align:middle line:84%
might say sorry, Dr. Muller,
but that's impossible.

00:21:56.180 --> 00:21:58.330 align:middle line:90%
It's not just love everybody.

00:21:58.330 --> 00:22:00.850 align:middle line:84%
But I shouldn't say
it's impossible.

00:22:00.850 --> 00:22:03.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Never say that's impossible.

00:22:03.110 --> 00:22:05.500 align:middle line:90%
This planet is our home.

00:22:05.500 --> 00:22:09.950 align:middle line:84%
Look, in Europe we were able
to suppress for 15 borders.

00:22:09.950 --> 00:22:13.404 align:middle line:84%
Now Europe is the love
of all the Europeans.

00:22:13.404 --> 00:22:14.820 align:middle line:84%
And they fought
each other before.

00:22:14.820 --> 00:22:16.870 align:middle line:10%
Now the French and
the Germans are--

00:22:16.870 --> 00:22:20.380 align:middle line:10%
they're married, or can
settle anywhere in Europe.

00:22:20.380 --> 00:22:22.930 align:middle line:10%
You have a European
Court of Human Rights.

00:22:22.930 --> 00:22:26.710 align:middle line:84%
And it's a miracle that
you have transformed

00:22:26.710 --> 00:22:31.360 align:middle line:84%
countries which killed each
other for all these centuries.

00:22:31.360 --> 00:22:33.290 align:middle line:90%
Now they are Europeans.

00:22:33.290 --> 00:22:34.090 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:22:34.090 --> 00:22:37.330 align:middle line:84%
Let me give you a
thought to consider.

00:22:37.330 --> 00:22:40.690 align:middle line:90%
You are a medical doctor.

00:22:40.690 --> 00:22:44.320 align:middle line:84%
The planet, Earth,
is your patient.

00:22:44.320 --> 00:22:46.120 align:middle line:90%
What's the prognosis?

00:22:46.120 --> 00:22:49.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, first of all, we have
a World Health Organization that

00:22:49.660 --> 00:22:52.870 align:middle line:84%
has all the works of the
doctors around the world.

00:22:52.870 --> 00:22:56.480 align:middle line:84%
I have recommended that we
should have an Earth Health

00:22:56.480 --> 00:22:57.610 align:middle line:90%
Organization.

00:22:57.610 --> 00:22:58.990 align:middle line:90%
>> An Earth Health--

00:22:58.990 --> 00:23:00.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Health Organization.

00:23:00.910 --> 00:23:03.600 align:middle line:84%
And that many people should
be the doctors of the Earth.

00:23:03.600 --> 00:23:04.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Excellent.

00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:06.680 align:middle line:90%
>> The healers of the earth.

00:23:06.680 --> 00:23:10.230 align:middle line:84%
The problems with the earth
are very, very serious.

00:23:10.230 --> 00:23:14.570 align:middle line:10%
We let every five
hours die a species.

00:23:14.570 --> 00:23:15.910 align:middle line:10%
Every five hours.

00:23:15.910 --> 00:23:16.710 align:middle line:10%
>> Really?

00:23:16.710 --> 00:23:17.970 align:middle line:10%
>> Every-- oh, yes.

00:23:17.970 --> 00:23:24.740 align:middle line:10%
Every minute we put 12,000 tons
of carbon dioxide into the air.

00:23:24.740 --> 00:23:27.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Let me get my head wrapped
around the species dying.

00:23:27.740 --> 00:23:30.320 align:middle line:84%
You mean like an eagle,
or a kind of a bird,

00:23:30.320 --> 00:23:31.520 align:middle line:90%
or a kind of a insect.

00:23:31.520 --> 00:23:34.000 align:middle line:84%
Every five hours one of
those species is gone?

00:23:34.000 --> 00:23:37.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Every five hours a complete
species on planet disappears.

00:23:37.680 --> 00:23:38.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Ugh.

00:23:38.480 --> 00:23:39.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Can you imagine?

00:23:39.680 --> 00:23:44.060 align:middle line:84%
When it took millions of
years to create that species.

00:23:44.060 --> 00:23:45.380 align:middle line:90%
>> I can't imagine it.

00:23:45.380 --> 00:23:48.080 align:middle line:84%
>> So there are now
six billion people.

00:23:48.080 --> 00:23:51.530 align:middle line:84%
In 1952 there were
two billion people.

00:23:51.530 --> 00:23:55.540 align:middle line:10%
In 2050-- in 50 years from now--

00:23:55.540 --> 00:23:59.810 align:middle line:10%
we will be three billion
more people on this planet.

00:23:59.810 --> 00:24:00.815 align:middle line:90%
>> Three billion?

00:24:00.815 --> 00:24:01.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Three billion.

00:24:01.710 --> 00:24:02.690 align:middle line:90%
Three billion.

00:24:02.690 --> 00:24:06.170 align:middle line:84%
That is half of the
world population of today

00:24:06.170 --> 00:24:07.670 align:middle line:90%
will be added to what we are.

00:24:07.670 --> 00:24:08.660 align:middle line:90%
We are six billion.

00:24:08.660 --> 00:24:12.080 align:middle line:84%
We are going to be 8.9
billion in the year 2050.

00:24:12.080 --> 00:24:16.280 align:middle line:84%
>> So then, doctor, the planet
Earth as your patient sounds

00:24:16.280 --> 00:24:19.580 align:middle line:84%
like it's sick and
getting sicker.

00:24:19.580 --> 00:24:21.940 align:middle line:90%
What do we do to heal it?

00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:23.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we're making
a lot of noise.

00:24:23.900 --> 00:24:27.400 align:middle line:84%
I created the first world
environment conference.

00:24:27.400 --> 00:24:31.250 align:middle line:84%
I brought together the first
world conference on the climate

00:24:31.250 --> 00:24:33.040 align:middle line:90%
in 1979.

00:24:33.040 --> 00:24:34.947 align:middle line:90%
And they say, Muller is crazy.

00:24:34.947 --> 00:24:36.530 align:middle line:84%
And what do you see
in the newspapers?

00:24:36.530 --> 00:24:38.210 align:middle line:84%
That now governments
are trying to save

00:24:38.210 --> 00:24:40.070 align:middle line:90%
the climate of this planet.

00:24:40.070 --> 00:24:44.090 align:middle line:84%
You see, we have done everything
in the preceding period--

00:24:44.090 --> 00:24:47.240 align:middle line:84%
humanity, humanity,
humanity, humanity.

00:24:47.240 --> 00:24:48.530 align:middle line:90%
And we have succeeded.

00:24:48.530 --> 00:24:51.440 align:middle line:84%
The longevity has increased
from 40 to 60 years

00:24:51.440 --> 00:24:53.990 align:middle line:90%
in the poor countries.

00:24:53.990 --> 00:24:57.210 align:middle line:84%
to 72 years in
the United States.

00:24:57.210 --> 00:25:01.070 align:middle line:84%
The children's mortality
has almost collapsed,

00:25:01.070 --> 00:25:02.630 align:middle line:90%
has almost disappeared.

00:25:02.630 --> 00:25:04.850 align:middle line:84%
There are no world
epidemics anymore.

00:25:04.850 --> 00:25:07.950 align:middle line:84%
We have done wonders
for humanity.

00:25:07.950 --> 00:25:10.490 align:middle line:84%
But we totally forgot
about the earth

00:25:10.490 --> 00:25:16.010 align:middle line:84%
until in 1972 we discovered that
something was getting wrong,

00:25:16.010 --> 00:25:18.260 align:middle line:84%
and it was called
the environment.

00:25:18.260 --> 00:25:21.860 align:middle line:10%
We have destroyed 30% of
the nature of this planet

00:25:21.860 --> 00:25:25.190 align:middle line:10%
since 1970, and we
continue to do it.

00:25:25.190 --> 00:25:27.770 align:middle line:84%
Now, on the world
scale it is horrible.

00:25:27.770 --> 00:25:32.252 align:middle line:84%
The earth now has become
pre-occupation number one.

