>> Of course, on these benches.

00:26:23.950 --> 00:26:27.230 align:middle line:84%
>> So tell me how I would
dream a dream on this bench.

00:26:27.230 --> 00:26:28.700 align:middle line:90%
How do I make it come true?

00:26:28.700 --> 00:26:31.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you take
two little rocks--

00:26:31.240 --> 00:26:33.085 align:middle line:84%
and there are some
available here--

00:26:33.085 --> 00:26:36.520 align:middle line:90%


00:26:36.520 --> 00:26:38.740 align:middle line:90%
you hold one in each hand.

00:26:38.740 --> 00:26:40.180 align:middle line:90%
>> One in each hand.

00:26:40.180 --> 00:26:46.470 align:middle line:84%
>> You hold them very, very
strongly with a lot of energy.

00:26:46.470 --> 00:26:52.750 align:middle line:84%
You close your eyes, and very
strongly you dream your dream.

00:26:52.750 --> 00:26:55.360 align:middle line:90%


00:26:55.360 --> 00:27:00.160 align:middle line:84%
And after a little while
you reopen your eyes.

00:27:00.160 --> 00:27:05.170 align:middle line:84%
And then you'll throw one of
the little pebbles on the earth,

00:27:05.170 --> 00:27:09.440 align:middle line:84%
so that Mother Earth will
help fulfill your dream.

00:27:09.440 --> 00:27:10.240 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:27:10.240 --> 00:27:13.310 align:middle line:84%
>> And the other one you keep
at home on your desk to remember

00:27:13.310 --> 00:27:14.440 align:middle line:90%
what your dream is.

00:27:14.440 --> 00:27:18.600 align:middle line:90%


00:27:18.600 --> 00:27:19.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Bravo.

00:27:19.400 --> 00:27:20.650 align:middle line:90%
>> So this is my dream.

00:27:20.650 --> 00:27:21.566 align:middle line:90%
>> That is your dream.

00:27:21.566 --> 00:27:24.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:27:24.310 --> 00:27:27.520 align:middle line:84%
Robert Muller's idea
for a Bench of Dreams

00:27:27.520 --> 00:27:30.970 align:middle line:84%
originated in the lush
countryside of Costa Rica,

00:27:30.970 --> 00:27:33.330 align:middle line:84%
where he spends
half of his time.

00:27:33.330 --> 00:27:35.830 align:middle line:84%
The rustic Muller farmhouse
can be found near Mt.

00:27:35.830 --> 00:27:39.190 align:middle line:84%
Rasur in an area
considered sacred

00:27:39.190 --> 00:27:40.485 align:middle line:90%
by the indigenous people.

00:27:40.485 --> 00:27:43.220 align:middle line:90%


00:27:43.220 --> 00:27:47.420 align:middle line:10%
>> Your University for
Peace in Costa Rica,

00:27:47.420 --> 00:27:50.570 align:middle line:10%
what does one learn when
one goes there as a student?

00:27:50.570 --> 00:27:52.440 align:middle line:10%
What is the purpose?

00:27:52.440 --> 00:27:53.925 align:middle line:10%
>> Peace.

00:27:53.925 --> 00:27:57.290 align:middle line:84%
To teach peace in
every possible way,

00:27:57.290 --> 00:28:00.210 align:middle line:84%
and to teach also
peace with the earth.

00:28:00.210 --> 00:28:05.000 align:middle line:10%
So in other words, that
there are two main purposes.

00:28:05.000 --> 00:28:07.790 align:middle line:84%
Avoid violence-- how
to avoid violence,

00:28:07.790 --> 00:28:10.490 align:middle line:84%
how to teach the children
not to be violent,

00:28:10.490 --> 00:28:12.740 align:middle line:84%
how to get peace
between nations,

00:28:12.740 --> 00:28:15.050 align:middle line:90%
to get peace between everybody.

00:28:15.050 --> 00:28:18.080 align:middle line:84%
And the second one is to
have the right relationship

00:28:18.080 --> 00:28:20.840 align:middle line:84%
with nature, and not
to destroy nature.

00:28:20.840 --> 00:28:24.050 align:middle line:84%
Because when we destroy nature
it's a war against nature.

00:28:24.050 --> 00:28:26.640 align:middle line:84%
>> So there would be classes
like environment, one on one.

00:28:26.640 --> 00:28:27.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, definitely.

00:28:27.440 --> 00:28:28.400 align:middle line:90%
Oh, definitely.

00:28:28.400 --> 00:28:29.740 align:middle line:10%
Definitely.

00:28:29.740 --> 00:28:32.870 align:middle line:10%
Now the students, they
have already a degree.

00:28:32.870 --> 00:28:36.200 align:middle line:84%
They have to have either a
master's degree or a PhD,

00:28:36.200 --> 00:28:37.700 align:middle line:84%
and they come from
around the world.

00:28:37.700 --> 00:28:43.880 align:middle line:84%
So that they get this additional
specialized teaching of helping

00:28:43.880 --> 00:28:45.890 align:middle line:90%
to have peace in the world.

00:28:45.890 --> 00:28:49.160 align:middle line:84%
And to create peace
ministries, and to have

00:28:49.160 --> 00:28:53.270 align:middle line:84%
peace education, whatever
you can in schools and so on.

00:28:53.270 --> 00:28:56.300 align:middle line:84%
>> And the students, after
they've graduated from

00:28:56.300 --> 00:28:59.970 align:middle line:84%
the Peace University in Costa
Rica, they go on to do what?

00:28:59.970 --> 00:29:02.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, they go into the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs.

00:29:02.270 --> 00:29:05.360 align:middle line:84%
They go into
various professions.

00:29:05.360 --> 00:29:07.460 align:middle line:84%
They go to a Peace
Corps, whatever.

00:29:07.460 --> 00:29:11.120 align:middle line:84%
That is up to them to find it,
but they have already an idea

00:29:11.120 --> 00:29:13.140 align:middle line:84%
before coming to the
University for Peace.

00:29:13.140 --> 00:29:14.780 align:middle line:84%
They have all
already an objective.

00:29:14.780 --> 00:29:16.700 align:middle line:84%
I want to go to the
University for Peace

00:29:16.700 --> 00:29:20.150 align:middle line:84%
because I want to work on peace
in the Ministry of Education,

00:29:20.150 --> 00:29:21.260 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:29:21.260 --> 00:29:23.720 align:middle line:84%
Or I want to go
into politics, and I

00:29:23.720 --> 00:29:26.550 align:middle line:84%
want to become a
peacemaker in politics.

00:29:26.550 --> 00:29:29.000 align:middle line:84%
Or I want to return
to central Africa

00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:31.250 align:middle line:84%
to make peace between
the ethnic groups.

00:29:31.250 --> 00:29:32.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Do you have heroes?

00:29:32.300 --> 00:29:34.240 align:middle line:84%
Do you have people you
look at it and you say,

00:29:34.240 --> 00:29:38.750 align:middle line:84%
what a wondrous, wondrous
human being he is--

00:29:38.750 --> 00:29:40.340 align:middle line:90%
or she is.

00:29:40.340 --> 00:29:42.506 align:middle line:90%
Who are your heroes?

00:29:42.506 --> 00:29:46.230 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I think a man
like Dag Hammarskjold,

00:29:46.230 --> 00:29:51.960 align:middle line:10%
who from being a tremendous
economist intellectual,

00:29:51.960 --> 00:29:55.080 align:middle line:10%
became a mystic in
the United Nations.

00:29:55.080 --> 00:29:56.940 align:middle line:90%
>> I agree.

00:29:56.940 --> 00:29:59.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Another man was
secretary-general, U Thant,

00:29:59.640 --> 00:30:03.540 align:middle line:84%
who was the Buddhist
mystic, who was very simple.

00:30:03.540 --> 00:30:07.080 align:middle line:84%
Very-- you cannot imagine
how simple he was.

00:30:07.080 --> 00:30:10.380 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes he said to me,
Robert, I cannot understand you

00:30:10.380 --> 00:30:14.730 align:middle line:84%
Westerners who go to the church
on Sunday to be spiritual

00:30:14.730 --> 00:30:16.080 align:middle line:90%
for an hour.

00:30:16.080 --> 00:30:20.490 align:middle line:84%
I am spiritual from the moment
I wake up until the evening when

00:30:20.490 --> 00:30:22.080 align:middle line:90%
I go to bed.

00:30:22.080 --> 00:30:25.060 align:middle line:90%
All my life is spirituality.

00:30:25.060 --> 00:30:28.050 align:middle line:84%
And I had to push him to
be strong as the Secretary

00:30:28.050 --> 00:30:29.250 align:middle line:90%
General.

00:30:29.250 --> 00:30:31.440 align:middle line:84%
And by the way,
speaking of dreams,

00:30:31.440 --> 00:30:33.690 align:middle line:84%
when I was appointed
to him people

00:30:33.690 --> 00:30:36.300 align:middle line:84%
told me, oh, he's only going
to stay two more years.

00:30:36.300 --> 00:30:38.489 align:middle line:90%
There's not much to expect.

00:30:38.489 --> 00:30:40.030 align:middle line:84%
And I said, but I'm
not going to lose

00:30:40.030 --> 00:30:43.990 align:middle line:84%
my time with a Secretary General
who is not audacious and so on.

00:30:43.990 --> 00:30:46.900 align:middle line:84%
So the first day
when we met I said,

00:30:46.900 --> 00:30:50.496 align:middle line:84%
do you have any
unfulfilled dreams?

00:30:50.496 --> 00:30:53.460 align:middle line:90%
He looked at me very surprised.

00:30:53.460 --> 00:30:56.010 align:middle line:84%
And he said, yes, I
have three dreams.

00:30:56.010 --> 00:30:58.400 align:middle line:90%
What are they?

00:30:58.400 --> 00:31:01.400 align:middle line:84%
I think that the United
Nations doesn't make sense

00:31:01.400 --> 00:31:06.420 align:middle line:84%
without China being here,
which is millions of people.

00:31:06.420 --> 00:31:09.050 align:middle line:84%
Secondly, I'm sick
and tired sometimes

00:31:09.050 --> 00:31:11.400 align:middle line:84%
to listen always to this
political and economic

00:31:11.400 --> 00:31:12.200 align:middle line:90%
speeches.

00:31:12.200 --> 00:31:15.080 align:middle line:84%
I would like to hear
a spiritual voice.

00:31:15.080 --> 00:31:17.390 align:middle line:90%
And thirdly, I would like--

00:31:17.390 --> 00:31:18.530 align:middle line:90%
I'm a teacher.

00:31:18.530 --> 00:31:21.140 align:middle line:84%
I think that without
teaching and education

00:31:21.140 --> 00:31:23.060 align:middle line:90%
we will have no peace.

00:31:23.060 --> 00:31:28.670 align:middle line:84%
So I would like to see maybe a
university for peace created.

00:31:28.670 --> 00:31:29.790 align:middle line:90%
And I said, OK.

00:31:29.790 --> 00:31:31.080 align:middle line:90%
Let's work on it.

00:31:31.080 --> 00:31:35.180 align:middle line:84%
First speech for him, return
of China to the United Nations.

00:31:35.180 --> 00:31:39.320 align:middle line:84%
Priority item number
one on the world agenda.

00:31:39.320 --> 00:31:42.320 align:middle line:84%
And China was voted
back to the UN.

00:31:42.320 --> 00:31:45.230 align:middle line:84%
And thank God to it,
because today we do not

00:31:45.230 --> 00:31:46.500 align:middle line:90%
have a Cold War with China.

00:31:46.500 --> 00:31:47.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:31:47.300 --> 00:31:49.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Can you imagine?

00:31:49.040 --> 00:31:53.240 align:middle line:10%
Secondly, I said
to him, look, you

00:31:53.240 --> 00:31:55.670 align:middle line:10%
can ask the pope
to come and speak.

00:31:55.670 --> 00:31:58.550 align:middle line:84%
He's the head of a little
state-- the Vatican state.

00:31:58.550 --> 00:32:00.110 align:middle line:90%
We can invite the pope to come.

00:32:00.110 --> 00:32:01.490 align:middle line:90%
He said, OK, wonderful.

00:32:01.490 --> 00:32:03.080 align:middle line:90%
You invite the pope.

00:32:03.080 --> 00:32:05.300 align:middle line:90%
I invited the Pope John Paul II.

00:32:05.300 --> 00:32:06.170 align:middle line:90%
He came.

00:32:06.170 --> 00:32:10.100 align:middle line:84%
I go all the Cardinals
assembled in front of him

00:32:10.100 --> 00:32:11.900 align:middle line:90%
in their garments.

00:32:11.900 --> 00:32:14.090 align:middle line:90%
And it was a wonderful day.

00:32:14.090 --> 00:32:17.660 align:middle line:84%
They asked me--
the pope would like

00:32:17.660 --> 00:32:21.200 align:middle line:84%
to give you a gift at
the end of his visit

00:32:21.200 --> 00:32:22.970 align:middle line:90%
to the United Nations.

00:32:22.970 --> 00:32:25.340 align:middle line:84%
What would you like
to get from him?

00:32:25.340 --> 00:32:28.370 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, I would like
to have a little crucifix--

00:32:28.370 --> 00:32:32.000 align:middle line:84%
very modest-- which
belong to himself.

00:32:32.000 --> 00:32:33.800 align:middle line:90%
And you know what he gave me?

00:32:33.800 --> 00:32:36.320 align:middle line:90%


00:32:36.320 --> 00:32:39.440 align:middle line:84%
This golden cross
which belonged to him.

00:32:39.440 --> 00:32:42.350 align:middle line:84%
That was the gift of the
pope for the invitation

00:32:42.350 --> 00:32:43.940 align:middle line:90%
to come to the United Nations.

00:32:43.940 --> 00:32:45.210 align:middle line:90%
>> The pope gave you this?

00:32:45.210 --> 00:32:46.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Gave me that cross.

00:32:46.250 --> 00:32:47.050 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:32:47.050 --> 00:32:50.740 align:middle line:90%


00:32:50.740 --> 00:32:52.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:32:52.670 --> 00:32:53.690 align:middle line:90%
What a wonderful dream.

00:32:53.690 --> 00:32:54.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Can you imagine?

00:32:54.740 --> 00:33:00.690 align:middle line:84%
And then finally, I got the
University for Peace created.

00:33:00.690 --> 00:33:05.100 align:middle line:84%
By that time, unfortunately,
U Thant had left, and died.

00:33:05.100 --> 00:33:07.710 align:middle line:90%
But we fulfilled his dream.

00:33:07.710 --> 00:33:13.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think that there would
be world peace if we all had

00:33:13.620 --> 00:33:17.640 align:middle line:90%
the same spiritual framework?

00:33:17.640 --> 00:33:19.950 align:middle line:90%
>> It would do enormously.

00:33:19.950 --> 00:33:22.350 align:middle line:84%
And it is now going
to happen at long

