00:35:56.880 --> 00:36:01.020 align:middle line:84%
But it's always-- you
must will to smile.

00:36:01.020 --> 00:36:02.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Isn't that interesting?

00:36:02.280 --> 00:36:04.490 align:middle line:84%
The mere mention of
him makes me smile.

00:36:04.490 --> 00:36:05.290 align:middle line:90%
>> You see?

00:36:05.290 --> 00:36:06.090 align:middle line:90%
>> [INAUDIBLE]

00:36:06.090 --> 00:36:08.560 align:middle line:84%
>> The president of a
country who always smiles.

00:36:08.560 --> 00:36:10.230 align:middle line:90%
>> That's lovely.

00:36:10.230 --> 00:36:12.060 align:middle line:90%
That's lovely.

00:36:12.060 --> 00:36:14.250 align:middle line:84%
How would you say is
the best way for us

00:36:14.250 --> 00:36:18.840 align:middle line:84%
to educate children to think
of the world in this way?

00:36:18.840 --> 00:36:21.120 align:middle line:90%
>> To decide to educate them.

00:36:21.120 --> 00:36:22.740 align:middle line:90%
That is the first step.

00:36:22.740 --> 00:36:26.460 align:middle line:84%
If you decide to educate
the children in peace

00:36:26.460 --> 00:36:30.750 align:middle line:84%
you will have so many
examples and models.

00:36:30.750 --> 00:36:34.830 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the things that I see
that is so distressing to me--

00:36:34.830 --> 00:36:38.100 align:middle line:84%
something simple--
toys for children,

00:36:38.100 --> 00:36:44.310 align:middle line:84%
video games for children, where
they are nothing but violence.

00:36:44.310 --> 00:36:47.010 align:middle line:90%
Nothing but killing.

00:36:47.010 --> 00:36:49.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think that
this should be avoided

00:36:49.650 --> 00:36:50.960 align:middle line:90%
by the parents.

00:36:50.960 --> 00:36:54.510 align:middle line:84%
They can do a lot
already by the teachers.

00:36:54.510 --> 00:36:57.450 align:middle line:84%
And there are
countries like Sweden

00:36:57.450 --> 00:37:01.920 align:middle line:84%
where they have even agreement
with the toy manufacturers

00:37:01.920 --> 00:37:08.380 align:middle line:84%
not to produce any
war and violence toys.

00:37:08.380 --> 00:37:09.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Really?

00:37:09.180 --> 00:37:13.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Now can you imagine that in
Sweden the toy manufacturers

00:37:13.980 --> 00:37:18.060 align:middle line:84%
are producing peace
toys and never war toys?

00:37:18.060 --> 00:37:18.900 align:middle line:90%
>> No war toys?

00:37:18.900 --> 00:37:20.970 align:middle line:84%
>> No war toys
anymore whatsoever.

00:37:20.970 --> 00:37:22.110 align:middle line:90%
They don't produce them.

00:37:22.110 --> 00:37:24.100 align:middle line:84%
So in Sweden you
cannot buy a war toy.

00:37:24.100 --> 00:37:24.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Really?

00:37:24.900 --> 00:37:25.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Or a war game.

00:37:25.830 --> 00:37:27.390 align:middle line:90%
It is all peace games.

00:37:27.390 --> 00:37:28.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Even their video games?

00:37:28.560 --> 00:37:29.700 align:middle line:90%
No squirt guns?

00:37:29.700 --> 00:37:30.010 align:middle line:90%
Nothing?

00:37:30.010 --> 00:37:30.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:37:30.750 --> 00:37:31.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Astonishing.

00:37:31.540 --> 00:37:33.664 align:middle line:84%
>> And that was an agreement
between the government

00:37:33.664 --> 00:37:34.890 align:middle line:90%
and the Swedes.

00:37:34.890 --> 00:37:37.480 align:middle line:84%
>> How many times have you been
nominated for the Nobel Peace

00:37:37.480 --> 00:37:38.280 align:middle line:90%
Prize?

00:37:38.280 --> 00:37:39.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, quite a few times.

00:37:39.640 --> 00:37:42.030 align:middle line:90%
Yes, quite a few.

00:37:42.030 --> 00:37:43.560 align:middle line:90%
Even by Nobel Prize winners.

00:37:43.560 --> 00:37:48.390 align:middle line:84%
And the nicest recommendation
for me as the Nobel Peace Prize

00:37:48.390 --> 00:37:50.410 align:middle line:84%
was from Betty
Williams, for what

00:37:50.410 --> 00:37:53.040 align:middle line:90%
I've done for the children.

00:37:53.040 --> 00:37:54.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Do you really not know?

00:37:54.890 --> 00:37:57.670 align:middle line:84%
Do you know it's about 19 times
that you've been nominated?

00:37:57.670 --> 00:37:58.470 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know.

00:37:58.470 --> 00:37:59.740 align:middle line:90%
Nobody told me this.

00:37:59.740 --> 00:38:01.210 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:38:01.210 --> 00:38:03.700 align:middle line:84%
>> You see again I come to
what I said at the beginning.

00:38:03.700 --> 00:38:08.560 align:middle line:84%
When you do something
positive some strange forces

00:38:08.560 --> 00:38:11.230 align:middle line:90%
begin to work in your direction.

00:38:11.230 --> 00:38:14.260 align:middle line:84%
And when you have dreams,
where you have ideas,

00:38:14.260 --> 00:38:18.370 align:middle line:84%
you are recompensed 10 times
by incredible happiness

00:38:18.370 --> 00:38:19.930 align:middle line:90%
and successes.

00:38:19.930 --> 00:38:23.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you know as I sit
here, enjoying immensely this

00:38:23.320 --> 00:38:29.110 align:middle line:84%
conversation with you, I'm very
aware of a phrase that you use

00:38:29.110 --> 00:38:30.430 align:middle line:90%
a lot.

00:38:30.430 --> 00:38:34.600 align:middle line:90%
You say, can you imagine?

00:38:34.600 --> 00:38:38.110 align:middle line:84%
And I realize that
is kind of a request

00:38:38.110 --> 00:38:40.600 align:middle line:90%
to go ahead and imagine it.

00:38:40.600 --> 00:38:43.430 align:middle line:84%
Because when we imagine
something what happens?

00:38:43.430 --> 00:38:44.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:38:44.230 --> 00:38:45.250 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:38:45.250 --> 00:38:46.450 align:middle line:90%
>> It occurs.

00:38:46.450 --> 00:38:48.210 align:middle line:90%
>> It's the first step.

00:38:48.210 --> 00:38:49.910 align:middle line:90%
It's the first step.

00:38:49.910 --> 00:38:51.770 align:middle line:84%
If you do not imagine
it will not happen.

00:38:51.770 --> 00:38:55.120 align:middle line:84%
I think this is the
value of the human being.

00:38:55.120 --> 00:38:57.590 align:middle line:90%
That he can imagine.

00:38:57.590 --> 00:38:59.680 align:middle line:90%
And then it becomes a reality.

00:38:59.680 --> 00:39:04.030 align:middle line:84%
>> Is your definition of
happiness different today than

00:39:04.030 --> 00:39:06.770 align:middle line:90%
it was 30 years ago?

00:39:06.770 --> 00:39:09.730 align:middle line:84%
>> I think it's the same,
but it's more expanded today.

00:39:09.730 --> 00:39:12.940 align:middle line:84%
I'm more optimistic
about a happy world

00:39:12.940 --> 00:39:15.940 align:middle line:84%
than I was when I came out
of the Second World War.

00:39:15.940 --> 00:39:17.540 align:middle line:90%
There's no doubt about it.

00:39:17.540 --> 00:39:20.320 align:middle line:84%
But we must keep in
mind that we have

00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:23.670 align:middle line:84%
completely new problems which
didn't exist at that time.

00:39:23.670 --> 00:39:25.270 align:middle line:84%
In the charter of
the United Nations

00:39:25.270 --> 00:39:28.420 align:middle line:84%
there's no word
"earth" or "nature."

00:39:28.420 --> 00:39:30.370 align:middle line:84%
That was not a
problem at the time.

00:39:30.370 --> 00:39:31.660 align:middle line:90%
>> That was what year?

00:39:31.660 --> 00:39:34.420 align:middle line:90%
>> That was in 1945.

00:39:34.420 --> 00:39:37.390 align:middle line:84%
By the way, we have
now the University

00:39:37.390 --> 00:39:39.880 align:middle line:84%
for Peace-- the
Earth Council, which

00:39:39.880 --> 00:39:41.860 align:middle line:84%
is located at the
University for Peace

00:39:41.860 --> 00:39:46.610 align:middle line:90%
has produced an Earth Charter.

00:39:46.610 --> 00:39:48.810 align:middle line:84%
So we have a United
Nations Charter,

00:39:48.810 --> 00:39:52.230 align:middle line:84%
and we have an Earth Charter,
where the earth is speaking.

00:39:52.230 --> 00:39:55.740 align:middle line:84%
And you will see in my
"Thousands of Ideas"

00:39:55.740 --> 00:39:58.270 align:middle line:84%
it's the Earth speaking
to me all the time.

00:39:58.270 --> 00:40:02.200 align:middle line:84%
Dear Robert, what do
they do this to me?

00:40:02.200 --> 00:40:04.640 align:middle line:84%
Whereas years ago, it
would have never have

00:40:04.640 --> 00:40:09.680 align:middle line:84%
occurred to me before 1972 even
to think so much for the Earth.

00:40:09.680 --> 00:40:12.620 align:middle line:90%
The earth was taken for granted.

00:40:12.620 --> 00:40:15.110 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the things that you
talk about that I actually

00:40:15.110 --> 00:40:17.960 align:middle line:84%
aspire to in your book
of "Ideas and Dreams,"

00:40:17.960 --> 00:40:20.720 align:middle line:84%
is the importance of
living more frugally--

00:40:20.720 --> 00:40:21.930 align:middle line:90%
in a more frugal way.

00:40:21.930 --> 00:40:22.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh yes, oh yes, oh yes.

00:40:22.110 --> 00:40:24.068 align:middle line:10%
>> Can you talk about
that a little bit for me?

00:40:24.068 --> 00:40:26.550 align:middle line:10%
>> That is absolutely essential.

00:40:26.550 --> 00:40:31.010 align:middle line:10%
Because a person in
the Western world

00:40:31.010 --> 00:40:35.880 align:middle line:10%
today consumes 30 times what
a person in a poor country

00:40:35.880 --> 00:40:36.680 align:middle line:10%
consumes.

00:40:36.680 --> 00:40:38.460 align:middle line:90%
Can you imagine?

00:40:38.460 --> 00:40:42.810 align:middle line:84%
And all the waste that goes
here in every direction.

00:40:42.810 --> 00:40:45.290 align:middle line:84%
One of the reasons why
the University for Peace

00:40:45.290 --> 00:40:48.540 align:middle line:84%
we have taken Saint
Francis as our Saint,

00:40:48.540 --> 00:40:51.230 align:middle line:84%
he has a beautiful
monument there--

00:40:51.230 --> 00:40:53.330 align:middle line:84%
it is because in
Saint Francis we

00:40:53.330 --> 00:40:57.170 align:middle line:84%
found the same ideals which we
have at University for Peace,

00:40:57.170 --> 00:41:03.660 align:middle line:84%
namely peace, respect,
and love for nature.

00:41:03.660 --> 00:41:06.760 align:middle line:90%
And simple and frugal living.

00:41:06.760 --> 00:41:09.420 align:middle line:84%
And for me, simple
and frugal living

00:41:09.420 --> 00:41:14.940 align:middle line:84%
is that it makes your
body function better.

00:41:14.940 --> 00:41:18.510 align:middle line:84%
And you are not
sold out to things.

00:41:18.510 --> 00:41:20.010 align:middle line:84%
>> But let's define
it a little bit.

00:41:20.010 --> 00:41:21.240 align:middle line:90%
Let's unpack a little bit.

00:41:21.240 --> 00:41:23.287 align:middle line:84%
Because people watching
this will say, well,

00:41:23.287 --> 00:41:24.120 align:middle line:90%
what does that mean?

00:41:24.120 --> 00:41:24.994 align:middle line:90%
We shouldn't go out--

00:41:24.994 --> 00:41:27.900 align:middle line:84%
>> It is not to waste
things as we do.

00:41:27.900 --> 00:41:30.480 align:middle line:90%


00:41:30.480 --> 00:41:34.460 align:middle line:90%
For example, to have cornflake--

00:41:34.460 --> 00:41:37.770 align:middle line:84%
to have something very easy
for breakfast in the morning.

00:41:37.770 --> 00:41:41.850 align:middle line:84%
Not hundreds of various,
various things around you.

00:41:41.850 --> 00:41:43.710 align:middle line:84%
I think everybody
knows what is is

00:41:43.710 --> 00:41:47.160 align:middle line:90%
to have a simple, frugal life.

00:41:47.160 --> 00:41:50.670 align:middle line:84%
And also, live more
generally in less things.

00:41:50.670 --> 00:41:55.980 align:middle line:84%
Even I myself, I have too
many things around myself.

00:41:55.980 --> 00:42:00.990 align:middle line:84%
And I refuse to live
in a modern house

00:42:00.990 --> 00:42:04.230 align:middle line:90%
on our mountain in Costa Rica.

00:42:04.230 --> 00:42:08.190 align:middle line:84%
It's an old peasant house
which I have restored.

00:42:08.190 --> 00:42:11.350 align:middle line:84%
And people say, why do
you live in this cabin?

00:42:11.350 --> 00:42:13.690 align:middle line:84%
Barbara, my wife, at
first she was shocked.

00:42:13.690 --> 00:42:16.800 align:middle line:84%
Today she doesn't want
to live anywhere else.

00:42:16.800 --> 00:42:19.740 align:middle line:84%
Because you can flood
a little dwelling,

00:42:19.740 --> 00:42:22.320 align:middle line:84%
a little cabin,
with all the love

00:42:22.320 --> 00:42:24.980 align:middle line:90%
of God and of the universe.

00:42:24.980 --> 00:42:26.570 align:middle line:84%
And the spirits
of the people who

00:42:26.570 --> 00:42:30.170 align:middle line:84%
lived there in the 19th
century, they are still around.

00:42:30.170 --> 00:42:33.200 align:middle line:84%
You can love something
which is very simple.

00:42:33.200 --> 00:42:39.110 align:middle line:84%
I prefer that simple cabin in
Costa Rica to a luxurious home.

00:42:39.110 --> 00:42:41.970 align:middle line:90%
So it's a kind of decision.

00:42:41.970 --> 00:42:45.140 align:middle line:84%
And I think the reason
of it is that you

00:42:45.140 --> 00:42:46.940 align:middle line:90%
want to be more yourself.

00:42:46.940 --> 00:42:49.250 align:middle line:90%
This is very, very important.

00:42:49.250 --> 00:42:50.150 align:middle line:90%
Inner self.

00:42:50.150 --> 00:42:52.700 align:middle line:84%
Here I have an anecdote,
which is important.

00:42:52.700 --> 00:42:58.820 align:middle line:84%
Not long ago there was a teacher
with a group of students.

00:42:58.820 --> 00:43:03.200 align:middle line:84%
And they said, oh, Mr. Muller,
what a wonderful nature

00:43:03.200 --> 00:43:06.140 align:middle line:90%
this university is located in.

00:43:06.140 --> 00:43:09.210 align:middle line:84%
And I said, yes, it is much
better than in a crowded city.

00:43:09.210 --> 00:43:12.590 align:middle line:84%
Here nature gives you
peace all the time.

00:43:12.590 --> 00:43:17.930 align:middle line:84%
You can look at this beautiful
nature without end, for hours.

00:43:17.930 --> 00:43:20.420 align:middle line:84%
Among my students
there is a girl--

00:43:20.420 --> 00:43:24.690 align:middle line:84%
a wonderful girl-- who
is always depressed.

00:43:24.690 --> 00:43:27.110 align:middle line:90%
Very, very unhappy.

00:43:27.110 --> 00:43:32.970 align:middle line:84%
I tried everything to make her
feel happy, and it didn't work.

00:43:32.970 --> 00:43:35.840 align:middle line:84%
And when she came
to this university

00:43:35.840 --> 00:43:37.820 align:middle line:90%
I said, let us not be inside.

00:43:37.820 --> 00:43:39.920 align:middle line:84%
Let us go outside in
the middle of nature.

00:43:39.920 --> 00:43:43.610 align:middle line:84%
Let's just sit down and look
at the beauty of nature.

00:43:43.610 --> 00:43:48.100 align:middle line:84%
And after a while I saw
that the girl was crying.

00:43:48.100 --> 00:43:49.570 align:middle line:84%
And I asked her,
what's happening?

00:43:49.570 --> 00:43:51.530 align:middle line:90%
Why do you cry?

00:43:51.530 --> 00:43:56.980 align:middle line:84%
She said, that's the first time
in my life that I found myself.

00:43:56.980 --> 00:43:58.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Can you imagine?

00:43:58.870 --> 00:44:05.220 align:middle line:84%
